main event: On April 11, 1965, a civilian witnessed an unidentified flying object in Corpus Christi, Texas, for approximately fifteen minutes.
interesting points: The object was observed flying from northwest to northeast,The conclusion of the sighting suggested it was likely a satellite sighting,The document dated May 5, 1967, mentioned that photographs submitted appeared genuine but could not be conclusively identified,The report included different forms of communication regarding the same sighting,Some communications emphasized the need for further information to evaluate the sightings.
